"Report" is more neutral in this case than "claim" since its about ancient sources & history than 2 opposing claims of individuals or groups. For example discussing ancient sources such as Herodotus, "report", "say" ,"assert" and the like are used rather than "claim" unless it's about presenting an account of 2 (or more) opposing individuals/groups. Also, "according to the sources" are more neutral than "assuming the sources are correct".

Changed the words "first Imam" to "first Shia Imam".

Reasoning: (1) Imam is a word that has some differences in understanding in the contexts of Sunni and Shia Islam.

(2) The several sects of Shia Islam undoubtedly choose Ali (the fourth Rashid'un Caliph) as their first Imam. The same isn't the case for the Sunni faction.

Hence the aforesaid phrase was modified to reduce ambiguity and maintain the sharing of authentic information.
